Package: DEMsimulation
Type: Package
Title: Simulates plausible versions of MERIT and SRTM DEMs in floodplains
Version: 0.1
Date: 2018-09-27
Authors@R: person("Laurence", "Hawker", email = "laurence.hawker@bristol.ac.uk",
  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Laurence Hawker <laurence.hawker@bristol.ac.uk>
URL: https://github.com/laurencehawker/DEMsimulation
BugReports: https://github.com/laurencehawker/DEMsimulation/issues
Description: Simulate plausible versions of a MERIT DEM or SRTM DEM for floodplains based on semi-variograms calculated for 20 floodplain locations. 
  DEMs can simulated by semi-variograms disaggregated by landcover class or using an 'average' floodplain semi-variogram. 
License: GPL-3
LazyData: true
Depends:
  raster,
  gstat
Suggests: rasterVis, RColorBrewer,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
RoxygenNote: 6.1.0
VignetteBuilder: knitr
